199 1st StLos Altos, CA 94022


        (650) 947-1600
    






The agency reviewed my insurance and saved me money. Their staff are friendly and always return my calls and emails quickly. I really like working with this agency!







Horrible incompetent fools!!! Twice now they have called me in a case of mistaken identity. First time was 4 years or so ago and second time was this week! They called me both times telling me I have a life insurance policy that needs updating and I insist that it NOT ME! Each time they put me through a bunch of crap and in the end after divulging someone else's personal information to me after my insisting that it's NOT my policy! Don't trust them with your personal information, obviously they are open to giving it out to the wrong people. 

I never had any life insurance policy with them. I had a auto and renters insurance policy with them and that was about 4 YEARS AGO! I canceled my policy with them because they managed to repeatedly screw up my policy by letting other people on my policy who were not the main policy holder go in and make unauthorized changes. Norvin and his staff were almost impossible to get a hold of. They raised my rates and would not fight for me after a accident that was not my fault. I asked them how I could get my rates down lower and they had me make changes that made my policy higher when they told me to take the other driver off my policy. The other driver was providing me a "good driver discount" which I lost after removing her upon their advice. 

I miss the days when Norvin Vogel's Allstate brokerage was owned by Gary Hellman. Gary and his wife knew what they were doing!







Wouldn't recommend. I have found Vogel and associates to be disconnected, lacking attention to detail and patronizing. 

Like most people I don't give my insurance a second thought and have wanted to change but it was never a high priority until now. I won't go into details except to say that because of how they handled a paperwork issue I was motivated to change agents and have started to shop around for other quotes.







I am rating Norv extremely poor because he is extremely non-responsive. By the way, I have never filed a claim so am an ideal customer. 

A copy of my policy is required to go to an Additional Interested Party. My policy says that a certificate of insurance has been sent to said party, but none seem to be received. 

I recently received an email from Norv requesting that I rate him "10" on an upcoming survey, and to contact them if I am not completely satisfied so they can address any concerns. I immediately replied to the email that the interested party says they have not received a certificate of insurance and to send me a copy if you did send it. No response. A few days later I received an email from Norv soliciting term life insurance. I immediately replied that he hadn't replied to my email. No response. Then I called Norv. Not in. Two weeks after my initial email, I received a call from his son saying Norv was out of town and has asked him to assist me. 

Based upon the above events, I have little faith that I would receive decent service in the event of a claim.







Specifically came to this Allstate office owned by Norvin Vogel since their website said they'd be open on Sat morning. If your website says you are open, you better be open during those promised times.  Showed up there and was completely eerie - lights in the hallway off and of course, no one in the office.

Bottom line: Lame. Update your freakin website. What's up with these Allstate agents who lie that they are open on Saturdays. 0 for 2.







Recently divorced, these folks have been fooling around promising me they would change the beneficiary on my Universal Life and nothing ever happens! The paperwork is done and despite numerous calls nothing gets done and I get no returned call! It has been an absolute nagging sore for 6 months....aaaagh!!!
MD Daly City







I worked with Elliott from this office and found him to be very professional and smooth in the transaction. I'd like to recommend this office for any insurance related transactions.







