I would like to thank this agency for pointing me in the right direction after a disastrous experience with another agency.  Specifically Alicia Hamilton, who searched and found me an agent who could help me continue my coverage even though her agency couldn't help me.  It's rare to find a company that will help you when there is nothing in it for them.  She truly understood my needs and went out of her way to help me.   I would recommend this agency to anyone looking for insurance.







High rates, unresponsive.  Heidi is horrible, she is nice to you when she's selling you a policy, as I wanted to get umbrella policy coverage.  She's terrible, not at all helpful, and insulting when you are asking a lot of questions to understand impact of an accident on your auto policy.  Raymond is no different, when I asked to be assigned to a different member of his staff to get a quote, did not not get a response.  I decided to move to a different agent.  In terms of rate, my auto policy went down and even got some refund on my condo after my policy was moved to the different agent.  there's a lot of allstate agents in the area, highly recommend to go work with those agency and avoid raymond and his team







Finally had enough of the high rates, arbitrary changes and minimal contact hours.

I found them to be minimally responsive and not friendly when making changes to the policy like adding or removing a car. 

But then when they made the change, they also made very arbitrary changes to the quote.  For instance, we dropped a car, which was the highest car on the policy, and found the price was still about the same.  They just made arbitrary changes to the other cars to make up for the dropped car.  Dropping the expensive sports car entirely didn't lower our bill.

Even in between bills arbitrary changes are made, but mysteriously it always ends up at about the same amount.  We had two bills a few months apart because we added two new cars.  In between the two bills, the amount for one car went down (with no explanation) by $300 and the amount for the other car went up (with no explanation) but $300.

I got fed up and decided to call AAA where we are already a member.  AAA gave an excellent price.  Allstate's price is 50% higher for less coverage.

But the thing that annoys me the most is the arbitrary changes so that they always get the same amount no matter what.

Oh, and another thing, the new AAA agent answered the call at 5:25 PM (answering machine at Barri at 5:05 PM) and then told me to call him as late as 11 PM.

Bye bye Allstate.  Hello AAA.







I have been with allstate for a long time. I generally call them for payment purpose and have been a good customer to them. But when I called them to inform them about removing a car from policy, they informed that they will prorate the amount and return me the rest of the policy money for the car. They promised they will follow up with an email which never happened. Its always that case with this agency. Finally I called again and I was informed that they will pay me some amount of money because my insurance increased to the other vehicles in that policy. I had to finally call them to cancel my policy. I went to get a quote from another insurance and its way to less than allstate.

Finally I wanted to talk to the management and I did not get any call from them.. Thats it - Good bye Allstate for the Mayhem you had created.







WORST EVER!!! 
Raise the rates and deny it (even though you have the bill!), tried to charge me $260.00 for two months when I didn't have a car!! I was late paying (my brother died suddenly & I still refused to pay that $260.) & they sent me to collections -- without that illegal $260!!! 
Terrible service, never call back, "lose" emails, "forget" to call -- blame you every time. 
Went to another agency got better coverage and WAY better rates.  

Do yourself a favor and go to a more professional and cheaper company. 

These people be nice as can be for your first check...and worst as can be after that!!







Wanted to recommend the Allstate Barri agency in Sunnyvale.  They are incredibly responsive (thank you Alicia for going in to office on a rainy Saturday to create a new PDF of policy for new car addition!).  Documentation is timely and helpful and they are always good about reviewing your policy and discussing options. Have had AAA, State Farm and others in the past & this Allstate team is really good.







Still with this terrible insurance agency. They don't pick up their phone, don't quote you the right numbers, and in my opinion generally provide some of the worst service I have ever seen inside or outside the insurance industry. I mean, how hard is it to quote correct car insurance costs on a Mazda?







