        3/11/2014
    

Finally had enough of the high rates, arbitrary changes and minimal contact hours.I found them to be minimally responsive and not friendly when making changes to the policy like adding or removing a car. But then when they made the change, they also made very arbitrary changes to the quote.  For instance, we dropped a car, which was the highest car on the policy, and found the price was still about the same.  They just made arbitrary changes to the other cars to make up for the dropped car.  Dropping the expensive sports car entirely didn't lower our bill.Even in between bills arbitrary changes are made, but mysteriously it always ends up at about the same amount.  We had two bills a few months apart because we added two new cars.  In between the two bills, the amount for one car went down (with no explanation) by $300 and the amount for the other car went up (with no explanation) but $300.I got fed up and decided to call AAA where we are already a member.  AAA gave an excellent price.  Allstate's price is 50% higher for less coverage.But the thing that annoys me the most is the arbitrary changes so that they always get the same amount no matter what.Oh, and another thing, the new AAA agent answered the call at 5:25 PM (answering machine at Barri at 5:05 PM) and then told me to call him as late as 11 PM.Bye bye Allstate.  Hello AAA.




